Match the information and example to the type of vulnerability listed below.

Design vulnerabilities

What it is: not be easily mitigated, may require mitigation in higher-layer protocols
Example: not considering security ramifications in the protocol

For the following attacks, match the name to its description and to its type of security vulnerability within the network taxonomy.

Packet Sniffing
What it is: capture all of the traffic on a network
Where it is in the taxonomy: Traffic based Attack

SYN Flood
What it is:  repeated, unfinished TCP three-way handshake connections
Where it is in the taxonomy: Protocol-Based Vulnerability 


True or False: Risk can be thought of as a relationship between vulnerabilities, threats, and impact.
True

